Temiloluwa O’Peters BOC Gases Nigeria Plc has announced the proposed sale of the controlling equity interest in the company by the United Kingdom-based BOC Holdings Limited. In a statement to the Nigerian Stock Exchange, signed by the Company Secretary, Gabinus Oriseh, BOC Gases Nigeria disclosed that BOC Holdings had entered into a binding share purchase agreement on Monday with TY Holdings Limited. According to the statement, BOC Holdings is the holder of 249,746,823 ordinary shares of the company, representing approximately 60 per cent of the issued share capital in the company. TY Holdings Limited is looking to acquire “the entire shareholding BOC UK holds in BOC Nigeria and certain claims owing by BOC Nigeria to BOC UK and certain other members of the Linde Plc group.” “We understand that the Proposed Transaction is currently at a preliminary stage and its consummation is subject to the requisite regulatory approvals being obtained from The NSE, the Nigerian Securities and Exchange Commission and the Federal Competition and Consumer Protection Commission in accordance with the Share Purchase Agreement,” BOC Gases Nigeria said. The company advised shareholders to exercise caution when dealing in its shares until a further announcement is made. Copyright PUNCH.
